00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:25.660
So we saw that
this is a problem,

00:08:25.660 --> 00:08:29.530
and in 2009, we added automated
captions to all the content

00:08:29.530 --> 00:08:33.970
on YouTube, which was an
awesome, awesome first start.

00:08:33.970 --> 00:08:38.190
But what about personal
videos, social media, podcasts?

00:08:38.190 --> 00:08:42.090
You know, the stuff that we
love to use each and every day.

00:08:42.090 --> 00:08:45.870
They're typically uncaptioned,
meaning for the deaf and hard

00:08:45.870 --> 00:08:49.140
of hearing, it's
effectively a silent movie.

00:08:49.140 --> 00:08:52.440
So led by the creative lab
in New York who is here

00:08:52.440 --> 00:08:56.490
today, we started exploring
a simple question--

00:08:56.490 --> 00:09:00.270
could we automatically
caption any media playing

00:09:00.270 --> 00:09:01.740
