00:26:43.540 --> 00:26:45.025
All right.

00:26:45.025 --> 00:26:49.480
[APPLAUSE]

00:26:49.480 --> 00:26:51.640
So as you saw in
that video, Lookout

00:26:51.640 --> 00:26:55.510
is able to detect and recognize
a variety of objects including

00:26:55.510 --> 00:26:58.480
currency and text through
computer vision and machine

00:26:58.480 --> 00:26:59.560
learning.

00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:01.810
Lookout uses several
image classifiers that

00:27:01.810 --> 00:27:04.070
run continuously on the device.

00:27:04.070 --> 00:27:06.880
This allows Lookout to process
video and provide results

00:27:06.880 --> 00:27:09.070
to users in near real time.

00:27:09.070 --> 00:27:11.740
Since information is
processed on device,

00:27:11.740 --> 00:27:14.290
Lookout can even work
in airplane mode.

00:27:14.290 --> 00:27:17.620
Results are also scored based on
a variety of signals, including

00:27:17.620 --> 00:27:19.010
user context.

00:27:19.010 --> 00:27:21.010
Our goal is to provide
the most relevant results

00:27:21.010 --> 00:27:24.300
to users in a timely manner.

00:27:24.300 --> 00:27:26.300
Lookout contains three modes--

00:27:26.300 --> 00:27:28.820
explore, shopping,
and quick read.

00:27:28.820 --> 00:27:32.270
It allows users to further
contextualize their environment

00:27:32.270 --> 00:27:34.790
and what kind of information
they want out of it.

00:27:34.790 --> 00:27:36.710
Explore is the most
widespread mode

00:27:36.710 --> 00:27:39.300
that can be used for a
variety of daily routines,

00:27:39.300 --> 00:27:42.440
such as cleaning the house,
cooking dinner, or visiting

00:27:42.440 --> 00:27:44.690
a new space for the first time.

00:27:44.690 --> 00:27:47.930
Shopping includes on-device
barcode lookup as well as

00:27:47.930 --> 00:27:49.790
currency detection.

00:27:49.790 --> 00:27:52.310
Quick read focuses
on text, and can

00:27:52.310 --> 00:27:54.950
be used for activities such
as going through the mail

00:27:54.950 --> 00:27:58.500
or reading labels on
items in the kitchen.

00:27:58.500 --> 00:28:00.770
Here's a quote from
one of our users.

00:28:00.770 --> 00:28:02.390
"I used Lookout
once in preparation

00:28:02.390 --> 00:28:03.620
for making spaghetti.

00:28:03.620 --> 00:28:05.780
It very accurately
describes each item

00:28:05.780 --> 00:28:08.120
without me having to maneuver
the device or struggle

00:28:08.120 --> 00:28:10.437
to get the items in focus."

00:28:10.437 --> 00:28:12.020
Finding the correct
ingredients to use

00:28:12.020 --> 00:28:14.810
when cooking is something
that many sighted users hardly

00:28:14.810 --> 00:28:15.950
think about.

00:28:15.950 --> 00:28:19.400
This shows how Lookout can be
used to really change lives

00:28:19.400 --> 00:28:21.740
by helping people who
are blind or low vision

00:28:21.740 --> 00:28:24.770
be more independent.

00:28:24.770 --> 00:28:29.330
You can find look out on
Google Play at g.co/lookoutapp.

